<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>CSP SLAP</h1>
        <h2>Content Security Policy Security Lab Attack Platform</h2>
        <p>Select a demonstration scenario to explore Content Security Policy implementations</p>
    </header>
    
    <main class="scenarios-grid">
        <% scenarios.forEach(scenario => { %>
            <div class="scenario-card">
                <h2><%= scenario.name %></h2>
                <p><%= scenario.description %></p>
                <a href="<%= scenario.path %>" class="demo-button">View Demo</a>
            </div>
        <% }) %>
    </main>
    
    <section class="demo-info">
        <h2>About CSP SLAP</h2>
        <p>CSP SLAP is an interactive security laboratory that demonstrates the progressive implementation of Content Security Policy (CSP) 
           from vulnerable applications to secure implementations using various techniques:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Vulnerable:</strong> No CSP protection - shows how XSS attacks work</li>
            <li><strong>Basic CSP:</strong> Simple script-src restrictions</li>
            <li><strong>Hash-based:</strong> SHA-256 hash allowlisting for inline scripts</li>
            <li><strong>NGINX Nonce:</strong> Legacy-friendly approach using NGINX sub_filter</li>
            <li><strong>Helmet Nonce:</strong> Application-level nonce generation</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</body>
</html>